supportDesc.extent: i, 143, i foliated leaves : 250 x 163 (197 x 113) mm; bound to 257 x 170 x 22 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 15 lines in two columns; border- and column-ruled.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Simple headpiece of blue and red rules (f. 1v); red border and column rules; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Brown marbled paper boards (type III) with reddish leather spine and corners; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in Dhū al-Qaʻdah 1251 A.H. (1836 CE) (f. 143r).

provenance: Gift of Professor A. Yohannan, Nov. 18, 1913 (note in pencil, f. 1r).
Formerly owned by Abraham Yohannan (note in pencil, f. 1r).
